      • getImpactSoundInsulation

        public Integer getImpactSoundInsulation()
        This specifies the required impact sound insulation performance for floors. The single figure target value is typically given in for in-situ field measurements (L'nTw) in decibels. The lower the L'nTw, the better the building element will attenuate impact noises. (Required)

      • getPrivacyRequirement

        public String getPrivacyRequirement()
        This specifies the acoustic privacy requirements of a space. Acoustic privacy for a space is rated according to the noise sensitivity of a receiving room and the level of activity noise within a source room. It is typically denoted by terms Not Private, Moderate and Confidential, and is used to determine the suitable level of sound insulation (DnT,w) for partitions between spaces. (Required)
